title: Grateful Dead Live at Rainbow Theater on 1981-10-04
lineage: Maxell XLIIS > Nakamichi DR-2 > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab > R8Brain > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transfer by Andrew F. Januray 2012
description:
Set 1

Jam-> Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil-> El Paso, Jack A Roe, Beat It On Down The Line, Brown Eyed Women-> Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, Let It Grow-> Deal

Set 2

Cold Rain & Snow-> Samson & Delilah, Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text:
Get it for the Samson alone! One of the finest of 1981. Brent is up front in the mix and bristling with energy. One of my all-time favorite shows.

Sean K.

Great recording of a great show! After hearing the other soundboard source that sounds distant and tinny, this one is just amazing.  Real crisp and up front.  Really makes you appreciate this excellent show that much more.
